Things like this can't really be rules to live by, but more like general guidlines to follow.  As seen above if someone wants to argue they will do a what if this or that is going on in order to paint a scenario to knock down the point trying to be made without actually adding any value to the discussion (man can you just see the egos bursting out?).  The best thing to do is try act as civil as you can in whatever situation you find yourself in.  Hopefully that will rub off on people you run across.  That is about all you can do. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=draxissdarkmare>Draxiss Darkmare</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:green;'>Tavern Patron</span></span><br>  Posts: 179<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(7/31/03 9:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntaverncommonsroom.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5294.topic&index=57>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: doh</span><hr size=1> Grundge, you cant say that you dont hold grudges, because you still wont let die what happened with us, and you still make those comments to mutual friends reguarding me...<br>
